---
layout: base.njk
title: Download
description: Download the latest release of Bòcan for macOS.
permalink: /download/
---

<div class="container container--narrow">
  <h1>Download {{ site.title }}</h1>
  <p>
    Notarised by Apple. Signed with a Developer ID. Stapled. Built for
    {{ site.architecture }}. No installer, no setup wizard, no telemetry. Drag,
    drop, double-click, listen.
  </p>

  <div class="dl-card">
    <h2>Latest release</h2>
    <p>
      <a class="btn btn--primary" href="{{ site.release.latest_download }}">
        Download {{ site.release.asset }}
      </a>
    </p>
    <p>
      <small>
        Always points at the newest stable release. Hosted on GitHub Releases.
      </small>
    </p>
    <div class="dl-meta">
      <span><strong>Platform:</strong> {{ site.minimumMacOS }} or later</span>
      <span><strong>Architecture:</strong> {{ site.architecture }}</span>
      <span><strong>Format:</strong> Signed disk image (.dmg)</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Older releases &amp; release notes</h2>
  <p>
    Every release, with checksums, signatures, and release notes, is on
    <a href="{{ site.release.all_releases_url }}" rel="external noopener">GitHub Releases</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Verify the download</h2>
  <p>
    Each release has a SHA-256 checksum file attached. To verify after
    downloading:
  </p>
  <pre><code>shasum -a 256 -c Bocan.dmg.sha256</code></pre>
  <p>
    macOS Gatekeeper does this automatically the first time you open it,
    courtesy of the stapled notarisation ticket. The checksum is for people
    who like belt <em>and</em> braces.
  </p>

  <h2>Install</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Open the disk image.</li>
    <li>Drag <strong>{{ site.title }}.app</strong> onto the Applications folder.</li>
    <li>Eject the disk image. Burn it ceremonially if you're feeling old-school.</li>
    <li>Open <strong>{{ site.title }}</strong> from Launchpad or Spotlight.</li>
    <li>Point it at your music folders. It'll do the rest.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Homebrew</h2>
  <p>
    Coming soon: <code>brew install --cask bocan</code>. We'll publish a tap
    once 1.0 ships and we trust ourselves not to push three updates a day.
  </p>

  <h2>Auto-update</h2>
  <p>
    {{ site.title }} ships with <a href="https://sparkle-project.org" rel="external noopener">Sparkle 2</a>.
    It checks for updates daily by default — silently, in the background, with
    EdDSA-signed verification. Turn it off in Preferences if you don't want
    that. Choose the <em>Beta</em> channel if you want fresh paint and
    occasional broken windows.
  </p>
</div>
